    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1899-11-01T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1899-11-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="64"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d64">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Señor <persName
                            type="to">Infante</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1899-11-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 1, 1899</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 24.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to the Department’s note of June 5 last
                    and your reply of the 8th of the same month, I have the honor to ask whether you
                    have received any information relative to the action of the Chilean congress in
                    the matter of the payment of the claim of the heirs of Patrick Shields.</p>
                <p>The Department hopes that the payment may be made at an early date.</p>
                <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
